pr_body:
Introduces a state backend for Hazelcast Jet using [RocksDB ](https://github.com/facebook/rocksdb) persistent storage.
Batch processors that require large state, more than available memory, and don't need cutting-edge throughput such as joins and aggregations would benefit from this feature.

This is Jet's project for [Google Summer of Code 2020](https://summerofcode.withgoogle.com/projects/#5385534219747328)
This project is mentored by @mtopolnik 

Note by mentor:
The goal of the work underlying this PR was primarily research. It exposed some gaps when introducing file operations to cooperative Jet processors. Further work is needed to close these gaps. This further work will happen after GSoC.

Note:
Work on this PR inspired #2469 introducing In-Memory sorting feature for Jet that will be included in 4.3 release.
